Run the project yourself (frontend + backend)
1) Start the backend (Flask)
Open Terminal and go to:
chatbot-backend/
Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the server:
python app.py
Backend will start on:

http://127.0.0.1:8000
It also uses Ollama (model phi3). If you don’t have Ollama running, the /analyze chat route will fail.

2) Run the frontend (static HTML)
Open:
chatbot-app/index.html
Recommended:

Use VS Code Live Server (or open in browser)
The frontend calls the backend at:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/...
Quick check (optional)
In a browser or via Terminal:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/ should return JSON like {"status":"running","model":"phi3"}
http://127.0.0.1:8000/fleet-summary should return the summary numbers.